Javascript

For Interactive websites

js is a programming or scripting language

Executes only in browser

Client side language

Javascript Engine - Script to machine code - 0, 1

v8 Engine - chrome, edge, opera
spidermonkey - firefox

ECMA Script - ES

Standard for Javascript
set of rules

variables

let a = 10;

let - keyword
let a; - declaration
let a = 10; - assign

rules for create variables:

should not start with numbers
special characters - $, _
should not use js keywords
unique
case sensitive

Data types:

1. Number = int 4, float 1.2, double 0.87758578257
2. String = "hello world" , 'hello'
3. Boolean = true, false

4. Null
5. Undefined

Operators: 

1. Arithmetic operators - +, -, *, **, /, %, ++, --
++ increment, -- decrement

2. Assignment operators - =, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, **=
3. Comparison Operator - ==, ===, !=, !==, >, <, >=, <=

4. Logical Operator - &&, ||, !
5. Bitwise Operator - &, |



















